cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.SI

This paper is about using federated learning to train machine learning models on medical data while preserving patient privacy. The paper specifically focuses on brain tumour segmentation, which is a task in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of differential privacy techniques to protect patient data falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also involves the use of machine learning algorithms (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to achieve its goals. Finally, the paper is concerned with the practical implementation and evaluation of federated learning systems, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SI).
